20 photos// 20 things I’m grateful for (feat. @turksandcaicos)

1. Unlimited beach time (be it Turks or Goa)
2. A partner that wouldn’t stop spoiling me
3. A partner that’s silly and makes me laugh
4. The freedom to pass out on a couch in the middle of the afternoon 
5. A healthy body (even though I might criticise it sometimes)
6. Art Therapy (we drew our spouses)
7. Savasana under the open sky
8. New friends
9. Being able to have a good laugh at something funny but also at myself when I mess up ever so often
10. Travel
11. Being able to eat at my favourite restaurants without having to think twice about money
12. Turtle watching!
13.  Being able to connect with 100 employees from a holiday
14. A puppy that’s lovingly waiting for me to get back from my holiday ASAP
15. Tan lines
16. Being able to stand on my head
17. Being able to move anytime, anywhere
18. Sunsets
19. Hotel rooms
20. More sunsets

latestPosts.caption:
There was a time I thought my body had to look a certain way to be worthy. 

No bloating. 
No folds.
No pigmentation. 
No stretch marks. 

I’m finally learning to stop editing myself out of my own life. Some days I still catch myself criticising the way I look and suck in my stomach before the camera rolls.
 Old habits. Old conditioning.
 But then I remember…this body shows up for me every single day. It lets me move, breathe, create, rest, feel. So no, it won’t always look “perfect” and I have to be kind to it because in a world full of mean relatives and random strangers on the internet that will always have something to say about it, I have to have my back!
 It’s mine and it’s enough, exactly the way it is💚

I celebrated International Yoga Day with THOUSANDS of New Yorkers at  Times Square and it was iconic!🗽

⚡️The energy was unreal⚡️

There’s truly no place like NYC. She’s chaotic, electric, magical and even though I’m not a big city girl, I really like her.

Even though sirens echoed in the distance and tourists filled up the whole space, the session was grounding and uplifting at the same time. 

I walked away with a free yoga mat, a cute AF tote and goodies that made it feel like a lil celebration🎁🧘🏽‍♀️

1. I share what I actually like and yes, sometimes that includes getting paid, because it’s called knowing your worth. If being honest and successful rubs you the wrong way, maybe ask yourself why that feels so personal.

2. Thanks for the unsolicited diagnosis, Doctor. Just say that it makes you uncomfortable when someone is so comfortable in their own bodies. 

3. Oh honey, plot twist: My husband’s the one with the Indian citizenship—guess love doesn’t always follow the passport you assume it does.

4. I must’ve missed the part where you were appointed gatekeeper of 5,000 years of tradition. I’ll keep practicing while you keep projecting.

5. I know how to turn my voice into value. You should try it too?

6. Lucky for both of us, I didn’t do my face for you.

Thanks to those who support..and to the rest, take a deep breath and maybe try healing instead of hating💚
